        "description": "Compute Voronoi diagram of circle centers using scipy.spatial.Voronoi. For each circle, the maximum possible radius is determined by: (1) half the distance to each Voronoi neighbor, (2) distance to Voronoi cell edges (for interior cells), (3) distance to unit square boundary (for boundary cells). Use Lloyd's algorithm: compute Voronoi diagram, move each center to centroid of its Voronoi cell (clipped to unit square), recompute radii, repeat until convergence. This naturally balances the packing and maximizes minimum distances.",
